The paper discusses the use of Blockchain technology in multi-agent robotic systems, which involves the intersection of several computer science subfields. The most likely category is cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems), as the paper focuses on the interaction between multiple agents and how Blockchain can improve their efficiency. The second likely category is cs.RO (Robotics), as the paper deals with the use of Blockchain in robotic systems. The third likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper discusses the use of Blockchain for trustless conditions and identifying intruders. The fourth likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as the paper discusses the deployment of distributed solutions and joint missions. The fifth likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper discusses the use of Blockchain to assess robot productivity and detect performance problems.
